Here's the specific issue with the potential NullPointerException (B003):

```java
public static Number getMaximumRangeValue(Dataset dataset) {
    // ...
    if (dataset instanceof CategoryDataset) {
        // ...
        return dataset.getMaxValue(rowKey, columnKey);
    }
    // ...
}
```

In this method, if the provided `dataset` is null, calling `dataset.getMaxValue(rowKey, columnKey)` will throw a NullPointerException. To fix this, add a null-check for the dataset before accessing its values:

```java
if (dataset instanceof CategoryDataset && dataset != null) {
    // ...
    return dataset.getMaxValue(rowKey, columnKey);
}
```

This way, the method will return null if the dataset is null, preventing a NullPointerException from being thrown.
